AGi - It had never been so clear, the President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen>, in his intentions on his alliance with the Italian Prime Minister, Giorgia Meloni>. At the debate between Spitzenkandidat (who did not participate in the right groups, Id and Ecr) traced its line. "Euro MPs to work with must meet three criteria: pro-Europe, pro-Ukraine (so anti-Putin) and pro-State of law", highlighted the candidate of the Ppe from the stage set up at the emicycle of the European Parliament in Brussels. What about Meloni? "I have worked very well with Giorgia Meloni in the European Council, as I do with all heads of state and government. It is my task as chairman of the committee. You are clearly Europeanist, you are against Putin>. It was very clear on this point and in favour of the rule of law, if this continues, we offer to work together," he said. And he also confirmed it in front of the red line threat posed by other allies.
&nbsp;
<div </div
